President Obama has proclaimed May 15, 2016, as Peace Officers Memorial Day and May 15 through May 21, 2016, as Police Week. This is a time to honor and express gratitude for the brave men and women who serve as law enforcement officers. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices they make to keep communities safe and highlights the importance of supporting and appreciating these dedicated professionals. The President also emphasizes the need for resources, training, and technology to enhance law enforcement agencies' capabilities. Additionally, he mentions the establishment of a Task Force on 21st Century Policing to build trust between communities and law enforcement. The President also discusses the signing of the Rafael Ramos and Wenjian Liu National Blue Alert Act, which aims to disseminate information about threats to officers. He calls for commonsense gun safety reforms to prevent criminals and dangerous individuals from accessing firearms. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to observe Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and for flags to be flown at half-staff.